def set_color(cetegories): 
    
    for category in cetegories: 
        
        adata.obs[category] = pd.Series(adata.obs[category], dtype='category')

        keys = list(color[category].keys())
        keys = list(set(keys) & set(adata.obs[category]))

        adata.obs[category] = adata.obs[category].cat.reorder_categories(keys, inplace=False)
        adata.uns[category+'_colors'] = np.array([color[category].get(key) for key in keys], dtype=object)

set_color(list(color.keys()))

Progenitor subsets¶

In [7]:
leiden_annotation = ['MPP (1)', 'MPP (2)', 'Baso (1)']
adata_1 = adata[adata.obs['leiden_annotation'].isin(leiden_annotation)].copy()
In [8]:
sc.pp.normalize_per_cell(adata_1)
sc.pp.log1p(adata_1)
In [9]:
def hvg_select(subset):

    adata_temp = adata_1
    adata_temp = adata_temp[adata_temp.obs['treatment']==subset]
    sc.pp.highly_variable_genes(adata_temp, min_mean=0.0125, max_mean=3, min_disp=0.5, batch_key='sample_rep')

    # Get hvg
    hvg = adata.var_names
    
    return(hvg)
In [10]:
hvg_nacl = hvg_select('NaCl')
hvg_cpg = hvg_select('CpG')

hvg = list(set(hvg_nacl) & set(hvg_cpg))
adata_1 = adata_1[:, hvg]
